<div><h3>MPA 3114 - Social Inequality in Politics and Public Administration </h3>  <p><hr>This course is designed and based around the subject of Social Inequality and how it is manifested in politics and public administration.  This course would be essential for students who seek to understand debates on social equality at the governmental and municipal level.  Students will explore the various dimensions of inequality, how it is defined, explored and measured, and what are the key social divisions are at both global, national, and local levels.  Class discussions will focus on not only identifying social inequity but explore various solutions to address systemic issues.</p>

